      ],
      "content": "<ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;a name=\"tblstor\"&gt;</ph><ph id=\"ph2\">&lt;/a&gt;</ph>Table Storage"
    },
    {
      "content": "Relational data is useful in many situations, but it's not always the right choice.",
      "pos": [
        15482,
        15565
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "If your application needs fast, simple access to very large amounts of loosely structured data, for instance, a relational database might not work well.",
      "pos": [
        15566,
        15718
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "A NoSQL technology is likely to be a better option.",
      "pos": [
        15719,
        15770
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Azure Table Storage is an example of this kind of NoSQL approach.",
      "pos": [
        15772,
        15837
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Despite its name, Table Storage doesn't support standard relational tables.",
      "pos": [
        15838,
        15913
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Instead, it provides what's known as a <bpt id=\"p1\">*</bpt>key/value store<ept id=\"p1\">*</ept>, associating a set of data with a particular key, then letting an application access that data by providing the key.",
      "pos": [
        15914,
