      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "The key has two parts: a <bpt id=\"p1\">*</bpt>partition key<ept id=\"p1\">*</ept> that identifies a specific partition and a <bpt id=\"p2\">*</bpt>row key<ept id=\"p2\">*</ept> that identifies an entity within that partition.",
      "pos": [
        17488,
        17630
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "In <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Figure 6<ept id=\"p1\">](#Fig6)</ept>, for example, the client requests the entity with partition key A and row key 3, and Table Storage returns that entity, including all of the properties it contains.",
      "pos": [
        17631,
        17816
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "This structure lets tables be big - a single table can contain up to 100 terabytes of data - and it allows fast access to the data they contain.",
